# Family Meal Planner — Cursor Rules

**How this file fits with `meal-planner.mdc`:** This file is the **main** project ruleset (what to read first, coding rules, key implementation files). **`meal-planner.mdc`** adds only **spec-file hygiene** (public `SPEC.md` vs gitignored `SPEC.local.md` vs `SPEC.local.example.md`, never leak private spec into code or commits). For `*.ts` / `*.tsx`, **both** files can apply together. **`meal-planner.mdc`** globs are **ts/tsx only**—for `*.css`, use this file’s Always read first + Rules; stack and product truth stay in **`SPEC.md`** / **`DESIGN.md`**, not in `meal-planner.mdc`.

## Always read first

- @SPEC.md — public product specification (canonical in this repo)
- @SPEC.local.md — private family overlay when present (gitignored; optional locally)
- @DESIGN.md
- @design-tokens.css

## Rules

- Never hardcode hex colours
- Never duplicate logic from `lib/meal-rules.ts` in components
- Never write business rules in API routes
- Always use semantic token names
- Mobile first — 390px viewport
- One file at a time
- Never put PII or `SPEC.local.md`-only details (real names, exact schedules, addresses, contacts) into **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`**—rules stay generic and safe to commit; private context stays in **`SPEC.local.md`** (gitignored).

## Key files

- `lib/meal-rules.ts` — business rules
- `lib/week-boundary.ts` — timezone
- `lib/shopping-utils.ts` — shopping types
- `design-tokens.css` — design system
- `SPEC.md` — public source of truth (product spec); `SPEC.local.md` for private details
